# Local dev needs NO Supabase config here. `pnpm dev` (scripts/dev.mjs) boots the
# local Supabase stack and wires the app to whatever URL + publishable key it
# reports — so a port change in supabase/config.toml is picked up automatically,
# with nothing to keep in sync. Copy this to .env.local only to override a default:
#
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# One-click Quick-login panel on /auth/login (student/traveller/admin/superadmin).
# `pnpm dev` defaults these on for local dev; set them here to change them.
NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_LOGINS=true
NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_PASSWORD=prophecy

# To point the LOCAL app at a hosted Supabase instead of the local stack,
# uncomment and set these — an explicit value here wins over the auto-derived
# local one. (This is also how a hosted deploy is configured; see deploy-prep.md.)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://<ref>.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# Optional site-wide HTTP Basic Auth gate (see proxy.ts). Leave UNSET locally.
# When set to "user:password", the middleware challenges every request before any
# app code runs — the edge gate that makes it safe to enable quick-login on a
# public demo without a paid Vercel plan. Server-only (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix).
# DEMO_BASIC_AUTH=reviewer:some-shared-secret
